/*do-while Loop in Java
Concept

A do-while loop executes the block of code at least once, even if the condition is false initially.

The condition is checked after execution.

Syntax
do {
    // code to execute
} while (condition);*/

Examples
import java.util.Scanner;

public class MAIN {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.print("Enter a number: ");
        int n = sc.nextInt(); // input number
        int i = 1;            // counter
        long fact = 1;        // factorial result (use long for larger numbers)

        // do-while loop to calculate factorial
        do {
            fact *= i;  // multiply current value
            i++;        // increment
        } while (i <= n);

        System.out.println("Factorial of " + n + " is: " + fact);
        sc.close();
    }
}
